nd recommend a settle\nment\nAt Detroit, business at the express\nterminal was tied lip tor the third\nday as 1,000 employes stayed out in\na strike initiated Monday. Although\n100 carloads of goods piled tip. offi\ncials said all perishable matter had\nbeen moved.\nIn New York. Daniel Harrison,\npresident of the local union, said in\nstructions had been sent to 12.000\nmetropolitan workers to halt opera\ntions at midnight tonight, 24 hours\nahead of the general strike schedule.\nW O. R. Hannan, superintendentj\nof the express agency's Washington\noffice, was confident that Mediation\nBoard action would be taken before\nthe hour the 1.200 employes here\nare scheduled in join the proposed\nnational walkout.\nAt least twice before, it was point\ned out. a similar strike notice had]\nbeen given bv the railway clerks\u2019;\nunion, and each tinv the White\nHouse averted strikes. Appointment\nof an emergency board automatical\nly would freeze the issues for at\nleast. 30 days, while the fact-find\ning board is at work.\nA spokesman for i he National\nMediation Board said policy lor\nbade him from saying whether the\ncase had been referred to lie White\nHouse, but said the matter was un\nder consideration.\nShould the strike go through\nabout 800 union members would\nwalk out here and probably would\nAuto Generators\ns-atui Starters\nK-XclmiMyr-d u /ti/e tjCu u>duC~\nLADIES\u2019 HATS\nCleaned or Retrimmed\nHAT TRIMMINGS\u2014FLOWERS\u2014\nFtatheri\u2014Ribbon!\u2014Veiling!\nHaf Frames\u2014Millinery Suppliei\nNew HATS IN ATTRACTIVE STYLES\nLADIES CAPITAL HAT SHOP\n508 11th St. N.W.\nM_Years Sn me Address)_XA. sm*\nV ENETIAN\nBlinds\nNOW!\nWOOD SLATS OR METAL BOND\nERIZED AND GALVANIZED\nSLATS\nQuick Deliveries\nSouthern Venetian Blind Co,\n2251 9th St. N W. Phone AD. 540<\n\u201cKeep Rollin' with Nolan\u201c\nNOLAN\nAUTOMOBILE\nLOANS\nPROCURED\nFavorable Rate*\nA'o Indorsers\n1102 New York Ave. N.W.\nBROKER\nGreyhound But Terminal\nrl. r;oo\nOpen Till 6 P.M\nWhether on